From 017d96ccb3294f8d0c74fb499b7ea1e34100fc18 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 16:09:12 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase D fix: flat-stacked DiffEditorWidget per file,
 content-sized

Reported: Tour shows no diff and Storyboard's diff is clipped
small. Both used `MultiDiffEditorWidget` which self-virtualises
and requires a fixed-size viewport. The `min-height` hosts I
picked clipped the content into small internally-scrolling cards,
and tour's grid layout compressed the host further.

The user's preferred shape: "make the diff view as tall as it
needs to be to show all the content." That fights the multi-diff
widget's design (it virtualises specifically because some PRs are
100+ files). For embedded in-pane use it's the wrong primitive.

New `KrtPrFlatDiff`: one `DiffEditorWidget` per file, each sized
to its `getContentHeight()`, stacked vertically. The outer pane is
the scroll surface -- same shape GitHub uses for PR diffs.

URI strategy is identical to the multi-diff path (file:// modified
+ krt-git:// original), so LSP and the native Comments API keep
working through the same code path. URI metadata registers with
`KrtPrCommentController`; `bumpDataProvider` fires 150ms after
mount so each editor's `editor.contrib.review` triggers initial
compute.

Switched all three call sites:
  - main Diff sub-mode (`renderDiffView`)
  - Tour mini-diffs (`renderTourMiniDiffs`)
  - Storyboard chapter diff panel (`renderStoryboardDiffPanel`)

`scrollToFile(path)` replaces the multi-diff's `revealFile(uri)`
for tree-row clicks.

CSS: `.krt-pr-flat-diff-card` for per-file cards (header strip +
auto-sized editor body). The editor body's height is set inline
by `getContentHeight()`.

`KrtPrMultiDiff` is now unused but kept in tree -- the Phase E
polish pass will delete it.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
